data.title: Finland
authors: Contributors to Eurovision Song Contest Wiki
data.meta_description: Finland has competed in the Contest 55 times since making its debut at the Eurovision Song Contest 1961 in Cannes. Their only win to date came at the 2006 Contest in Athens when hard rock band Lordi won, ending a 45-year wait for their first victory. The country has finished last a total of ten...
